propOverrides.description:
Map of displayName → style patches. Each value can have { className, props } keys.

Example:
  {"Section": {"className": "bg-primary py-space-xl"}, "Card": {"className": "rounded-xl shadow-lg"}}

nodes.description:
Flat CraftJS node map: { nodeId: nodeDefinition, ... }. Each node definition must include:

  {
    "type": { "resolvedName": "Container" },  // Component type
    "isCanvas": true,                          // true if it can have children
    "props": {
      "canDelete": true,
      "canEditName": true,
      "type": "section",                       // "section" for root, omit for children
      "className": "flex flex-col w-full py-space-lg px-container-x bg-primary",
      "custom": { "displayName": "My Block" }
    },
    "parent": "page_home",                     // parent node ID
    "nodes": ["child_id_1", "child_id_2"],     // ordered child IDs
    "linkedNodes": {}
  }

All styling uses props.className — a single Tailwind class string. Mobile-first: unprefixed = base/mobile, md: = desktop, sm: = tablet.

Available component types: Container, Text, Image, Button, ButtonList, ImageList, List, ListItem, Table, TableSection, TableRow, TableCell, Form, FormElement, Divider, Spacer, Video, Audio, Embed.
Use get_component_schema for full prop details.

node.description:
Node definition. Must include:
  type: { resolvedName: "Text" | "Container" | "Image" | "Button" | "ButtonList" | "List" | "ListItem" | etc }
  isCanvas: true (containers) or false (leaf elements)
  props: { canDelete: true, canEditName: true, className: "flex flex-col gap-4 ...", text/src/etc, custom: { displayName: "..." } }

parent and linkedNodes are set automatically — do not include them.
